==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ataxic
<hw>A*tax"ic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ataxique</ets>. See <er>Ataxia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Characterized by ataxy, that is, <sd>(a)</sd> by great irregularity
of functions or symptoms, or <sd>(b)</sd> by a lack of coordinating
power in movements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ataxic fever</b></col>, <cd>malignant typhus fever.</cd>
<rj><au>Pinel.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atazir</ent>⟦br⟧
